 "closingNote": null,
 "draftNote": "4 of five queued off a bottom-two lane: Mr_Meat31 (midlane→offlane), Cuban Noobster (jungle→carry), Willy Guggenheim (offlane→jungle), Xeebs (support→jungle).",
 "coaching": {
  "headline": "An off-role scramble that didn't hold — objectives lost 21k–75k, three lanes behind, and only The Fey mid stayed afloat.",
  "team": "Four of five queued off their main this game — Cuban jungle (he's a carry), Goldilocks carry (an offlaner), Xeebs support (your jungler), Willy offlane (your support) — and it showed: three lanes were 'theirs all game' and the objective war went 21k–75k against you. Mr_Meat31's The Fey was the only anchor (4/5/8, team-high 36.6k). Stacking off-roles costs you both the matchups and your comfort picks. Two recurring fixes: queue mains when you can, and someone needs to itemize armor — for the second game running, only 1/5 of you built it into a physical-heavy enemy (their Murdock did 34k).",
  "whatShiftedIt": "Off-roles into losing lanes, then out-macro'd. Four mains were out of position, three lanes fell behind, and you lost the objective war 21k–75k. If you must flex, draft the in-pool counter for the lane — not a comfort pick that loses the matchup.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "7c8ab99c-31c5-4ea5-a6fa-e0d6417c3f1b": "The Fey mid, 4/5/8 and team-high 36.6k — won your lane (favored vs Morigesh) and carried the damage. The only player on-comfort, and it showed. Nothing to fix.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "Zinx into Rampage offlane (your off-role) was 'theirs all game' — 5/10/3, ten deaths into a losing matchup. If you flex offlane, Steel is a +6 counter to Rampage (and it's in the pool); otherwise stay support where you're strongest.",
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Khaimera jungle (off-role — you're the carry) 3/10/2, ten deaths, and you skipped armor into a 3-physical comp. Off-role jungle is a big ask; if the team needs it, build the armor (Basilisk/Rapture) and reset instead of forcing.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "Drongo carry (off-role) 2/8/4 into an even Murdock lane — eight deaths and an unfinished core (no Vanquisher/Imperator). That lane was winnable; complete the core and play it tighter before forcing fights.",
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Argus support (off-role — you're the jungler) 2/6/8 into a losing Aurora. The team missed your Khaimera jungle — which Cuban ended up forcing off-role instead. Swapping you and Cuban back fixes two lanes at once."
  }
 },
